<h2>About</h2>
<p style="margin-top: 1rem;">UQ Open Source Notes is a community-driven project providing free, open course notes for University of Queensland students.</p>

<h3 style="margin-top: 1.5rem;">How it works</h3>
<p style="margin-top: 0.5rem;">Notes are written in <a href="https://typst.app">Typst</a> and compiled to PDF automatically via GitHub Actions whenever changes are pushed. The site updates with every new PDF.</p>

<h3 style="margin-top: 1.5rem;">Contributing</h3>
<p style="margin-top: 0.5rem;">All notes are hosted on <a href="https://github.com/UQOSNotes/notes">GitHub</a>. Fork the repo, add your notes for a course, and open a pull request.</p>
